The spectator is supposed to be on the couch, which must be in the middle of the room in order to command these separate views. miscet cannot mean that out of any one window he could see the three different prospects blended, but that from his couch in the middle of the room he could take one sweeping, comprehensive view of these prospects.

22. interiacens andron. “An intervening passage separates the wall of the chamber from that of the garden.'’ Andron in Greek means the men’s apartment; in Latin it means a passage or corridor connecting two rooms in a house, or, as here, a passage between two walls.
